Class Behavior

  • java.lang.Object
    • generationModele.Behavior

  • public class Behavior
extends java.lang.Object
    A behavior defines the behavior of an agent`

    A behavior consists of :

    • A norm mother on which the parameters are built
    • A HashMap of Instantiated Parameters

    • Constructor Detail

      • Behavior

        public Behavior(Norm normMother)
        Behavior Constructor. You must specify the norm mother. All the parameters which compose the norm and the other institutional parameters which are not specified by the norm are added to the behavior. Their values are not set. They will be set by the generationEngine.
        Parameters:
        normMother - The norm mother
        See Also:
        generationEngine, Norm, normMother, InstantiatedParameter
